				<h1>Roving vagabonds</h1>
				
					<p>Followed <a href="http://swaroopch.info">Swaroop</a> to <a href="http://www.gadling.com/">gadling.com</a> . Whoa! a really neat site on adventure travelling.  You have to browse it to believe it. I&#8217;ll not be surprised if this site gets added to your daily news roll.</p>

	<p><a href="http://bootsnall.com">BootsnAll</a> is another interesting travel site. It has loads of information on places of interest from all the continents, and information on logistics and stuff. </p>

	<p>Even if you not planning to travel anytime soon, read the travelogues. Some of them are quite <a href="http://www.bootsnall.com/articles/04-12/is-it-safe-going-to-the-dentist-in-india-or-dental-healthcare-tourism.html">entertaining</a><br />
